Only the part of the file chemical-disease association (with directEvidence: therapeutic or marker/mechanism) is integrated into neo4j and only a part of exposure-event association (only with positive correlation with outcome).
It took further information from chemical vocabulary and disease vocabulary.
This was executed with python 3.5.3 on windows. 
Program need path to ctd data.

I use the file from June 2017.
The files can be downloaded by http://ctdbase.org/downloads/.

Davis AP, Grondin CJ, Johnson RJ, Sciaky D, King BL, McMorran R, Wiegers J, Wiegers TC, Mattingly CJ. The Comparative Toxicogenomics Database: update 2017. Nucleic Acids Res. 2016 Sep 19;[Epub ahead of print] 
